Why are some people able to eat whatever they want and never put on a pound?
Sure you can starve yourself, workout and lose the weight, but you always have to live in fear that it will come back, constantly stress about what to eat and monitor your intake. You don't deserve to live like that.
So the question is, what’s the difference between your body and the body of someone who does not gain weight? The answer is their rate of metabolism.
Metabolism is how fast the body burns energy. With a high metabolism it is impossible to gain weight and you never have to worry about what you eat.
Your body is programmed to convert and store energy as fat. You want to change that program, so essentially your body does the work for you and constantly burns that extra energy so you never have to think about your weight again.
Sounds like a dream? Just look at that slim person who eats that huge piece of chocolate cake without a care. They’re not thinking about their weight. This is proof that the answer to permanent weight-loss is boosting your metabolism.
